  "prompt": "What are the biggest frustrations that people have about their boyfriends?",
  "response": "Some common frustrations people have about their boyfriends include:\n\n1. Poor communication\n- Not opening up emotionally\n- Not listening actively\n- Avoiding serious conversations\n\n2. Lack of effort in the relationship\n- Not planning dates\n- Not showing appreciation\n- Not helping with responsibilities\n\n3. Time management issues\n- Being too busy for the relationship\n- Spending excessive time with friends/gaming\n- Not prioritizing quality time together\n\n4. Immaturity\n- Not being responsible\n- Avoiding commitment\n- Childish behavior\n\n5. Technology distractions\n- Excessive phone/social media use\n- Ignoring partner while on devices\n\n6. Financial irresponsibility\n- Poor money management\n- Overspending\n- Not contributing equally\n\n7. Lack of emotional support\n- Not being empathetic\n- Dismissing partner's feelings\n- Not providing comfort during difficult times\n\n8. Inconsistent behavior\n- Mixed signals\n- Unpredictable mood swings\n- Unreliability\n\n9. Jealousy or trust issues\n- Inappropriate interactions with others\n- Lack of transparency\n- Suspicious behavior\n\n10. Different life goals/values\n- Misaligned future plans\n- Conflicting relationship expectations\n\nNote: These frustrations can vary depending on individual personalities and relationship dynamics.",
